<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="268" pageId="1" pageNumber="267" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1697,1977]" box="[151,1013,1697,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1697,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">Description.</emphasis>
Body yellowish, eyes black medially and yellowish marginally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1697,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">
Abdominal apodemes (
<figureCitation box="[459,521,1736,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[184,1436,189,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1449,179,1784]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hepneriana applanata sp. nov. a. anal tube appendage and pygofer side, lateral view; b. subgenital plate, style, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, caudal view; e. aedeagus, lateral view; f. abdominal apodemes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166904/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
f) broad, apical margin rounded, extended to middle part of 3rd sternite. Anal tube appendage (
<figureCitation box="[286,349,1772,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[184,1436,189,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1449,179,1784]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hepneriana applanata sp. nov. a. anal tube appendage and pygofer side, lateral view; b. subgenital plate, style, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, caudal view; e. aedeagus, lateral view; f. abdominal apodemes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166904/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
a) short, with ventral margin concave.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1697,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">
Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[400,465,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[184,1436,189,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1449,179,1784]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hepneriana applanata sp. nov. a. anal tube appendage and pygofer side, lateral view; b. subgenital plate, style, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, caudal view; e. aedeagus, lateral view; f. abdominal apodemes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166904/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
b) truncate apically, without distinct protrusion on outer margin. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1352,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[184,1436,189,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1449,179,1784]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hepneriana applanata sp. nov. a. anal tube appendage and pygofer side, lateral view; b. subgenital plate, style, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, caudal view; e. aedeagus, lateral view; f. abdominal apodemes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166904/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
c) with club-shaped process much shorter than lamellar process, lamellar process relatively broad, with distinct triangular ridge perpendicular to lamella on ventral side, apical margin rounded with sides expanded. Aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1412,1880,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[184,1436,189,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1449,179,1784]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hepneriana applanata sp. nov. a. anal tube appendage and pygofer side, lateral view; b. subgenital plate, style, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, caudal view; e. aedeagus, lateral view; f. abdominal apodemes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166904/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="267">Figs 1</figureCitation>
d, e) broad and depressed, lateral sides curved caudad, with flange on meso-dorsal margin, paired subapical processes broad and serrated on outer apical margin; preatrial process relatively slim, apical part S-shaped.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166904/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="268" targetBox="[184,1436,189,1768]" targetPageId="2">
